<subSubSection lastPageId="7" pageId="4" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1388,2025]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1388,1413]" pageId="4">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[276,361,1388,1413]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1229,1252]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,193,1208]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1247,193,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 22. Cocoons and adults. 13, 14, Stigmella lamiacifoliae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., cocoons; 15, same, forewing of male holotype; 16, same, male holotype, general view; 17, same, male paratype; 18, Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., female paratype; 19, same, male holotype; 20, same, forewing of female paratype; 21, 22, same, cocoons" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035610/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Forewing length about 2.0– 
<quantity box="[697,786,1389,1413]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
; wingspan about 
<quantity box="[984,1123,1388,1413]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.55" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="4.55" valueMax="4.6" valueMin="4.5">4.5–4.6 mm</quantity>
. Head: palpi cream to grey, glossy; frontal tuft ferruginous; collar grey, silvery glossy; scape white to cream, very glossy; antenna slightly longer than half the length of forewing; flagellum with about 35 segments, dark grey with some purple iridescence on upper side and underside. Thorax and tegula dull brass to brown. Forewing: area proximal to fascia dull brass or bronze shading into dark brown with some purple iridescence; fascia postmedian, silvery, widening on tornus; area distal to fascia dark brown with strong purple iridescence and usually with some silvery scales overlapping fringe; terminal and tornal fringe dark brown with some gloden gloss; underside of forewing fuscous, without spots or androconia. Hindwing grey with some golden gloss and purple iridescence on upper side, dark grey on underside, without androconia; fringe grey. Legs silvery cream to grey, laterally fuscous. Abdomen fuscous with purple iridescence on upper side, silvery cream to grey cream on underside; anal tufts fuscous, very short, indistinctive; genital plates cream.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1388,2025]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1784,1809]" pageId="4">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[304,443,1784,1809]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1229,1252]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,193,1208]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1247,193,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 22. Cocoons and adults. 13, 14, Stigmella lamiacifoliae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., cocoons; 15, same, forewing of male holotype; 16, same, male holotype, general view; 17, same, male paratype; 18, Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., female paratype; 19, same, male holotype; 20, same, forewing of female paratype; 21, 22, same, cocoons" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035610/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Figs 18, 20</figureCitation>
). Similar to male. Number of segments of flagellum remains unknown (antennae are broken in the female 
<typeStatus box="[389,501,1821,1845]" pageId="4">paratypes</typeStatus>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1388,2025]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,285]" lastPageId="5" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,372,1856,1881]" pageId="4">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[389,522,1856,1881]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,197,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[153,1433,195,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 53. Male genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide RA 653 (ZMUC). 46 – 50, capsule without phallus; 51 – 53, phallus (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035620/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Figs 46–53</figureCitation>
). Capsule distinctly longer (280 µm) than wide (135 µm). Vinculum very long, with long lateral lobes. Uncus strongly thickened, with three small notches caudally (
<figureCitation box="[1126,1212,1892,1917]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,197,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[153,1433,195,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 53. Male genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide RA 653 (ZMUC). 46 – 50, capsule without phallus; 51 – 53, phallus (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035620/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
). Gnathos with two caudal processes slightly widening basally (
<figureCitation box="[643,724,1928,1953]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,197,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[153,1433,195,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 53. Male genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide RA 653 (ZMUC). 46 – 50, capsule without phallus; 51 – 53, phallus (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035620/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
) and rather large central plate. Valva (
<figureCitation box="[1153,1323,1928,1953]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,197,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[153,1433,195,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 53. Male genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide RA 653 (ZMUC). 46 – 50, capsule without phallus; 51 – 53, phallus (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035620/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Figs 47, 49, 50</figureCitation>
) 120–130 µm long, 55–70 µm wide, with two large apical processes and one protruding dorsal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1260,1964,1989]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,197,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[153,1433,195,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 53. Male genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide RA 653 (ZMUC). 46 – 50, capsule without phallus; 51 – 53, phallus (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035620/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
); transtilla with triangularly shaped, lobe-like sublateral processes (
<figureCitation box="[733,819,2000,2025]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,197,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[153,1433,195,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 53. Male genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide RA 653 (ZMUC). 46 – 50, capsule without phallus; 51 – 53, phallus (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035620/files/figure.png" pageId="4">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Juxta absent or fully membranous (not visible in the permanent mounts of the 
<typeStatus box="[437,485,152,176]" pageId="5">type</typeStatus>
series). Chitinized tube of phallus (
<figureCitation box="[884,1011,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,197,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[153,1433,195,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 53. Male genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide RA 653 (ZMUC). 46 – 50, capsule without phallus; 51 – 53, phallus (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035620/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Figs 51–53</figureCitation>
) 160–190 µm long, 70 µm wide, with three spine-like carinae (
<figureCitation box="[432,566,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,197,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[153,1433,195,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 53. Male genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide RA 653 (ZMUC). 46 – 50, capsule without phallus; 51 – 53, phallus (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035620/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Figs 51, 52</figureCitation>
); vesica with 9–10 large spine-like cornuti including a curved one (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,197,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[153,1433,195,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 53. Male genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide RA 653 (ZMUC). 46 – 50, capsule without phallus; 51 – 53, phallus (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035620/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
), and with a distal cluster of 11 weaker chitinized spine-like cornuti (
<figureCitation box="[905,988,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,197,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[153,1433,195,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 53. Male genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide RA 653 (ZMUC). 46 – 50, capsule without phallus; 51 – 53, phallus (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035620/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
); there are also numerous minute spinelike cornuti on vesica (
<figureCitation box="[407,490,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,197,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[153,1433,195,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 53. Male genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., holotype, genitalia slide RA 653 (ZMUC). 46 – 50, capsule without phallus; 51 – 53, phallus (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035620/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
