<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1752,2029]" pageId="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,398,1752,1777]" pageId="6">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[416,549,1752,1777]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1450,1473]" captionTargetBox="[313,1269,195,1429]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[313,1273,193,1429]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 57. Female genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 54, genitalia slide no. RA 655, paratype, apophyses; 55, same, bursa copulatrix; 56, genitalia slide no. RA 654, paratype, general view; 57, genitalia slide no. RA 655, paratype, comb-like pectinations on corpus bursae (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035622/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figs 54–57</figureCitation>
). Total length about 835 µm. Anterior and posterior apophyses similar in the lenght; anterior apophyses distictly wide, posterior ones very slender. Vestibulum without sclerites. Corpus bursae with large folded distal part and 250 µm wide, oval shaped basal part with numerous comb-like pectinations (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1450,1473]" captionTargetBox="[313,1269,195,1429]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[313,1273,193,1429]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 57. Female genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 54, genitalia slide no. RA 655, paratype, apophyses; 55, same, bursa copulatrix; 56, genitalia slide no. RA 654, paratype, general view; 57, genitalia slide no. RA 655, paratype, comb-like pectinations on corpus bursae (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035622/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
). Accessory sac very large; ductus spermathecae without coils (
<figureCitation box="[918,1005,1860,1885]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1450,1473]" captionTargetBox="[313,1269,195,1429]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[313,1273,193,1429]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 57. Female genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 54, genitalia slide no. RA 655, paratype, apophyses; 55, same, bursa copulatrix; 56, genitalia slide no. RA 654, paratype, general view; 57, genitalia slide no. RA 655, paratype, comb-like pectinations on corpus bursae (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035622/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
). Abdominal apex slender, narrowing distally (
<figureCitation box="[248,379,1896,1921]" captionStart="FIGURES 54 – 57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1450,1473]" captionTargetBox="[313,1269,195,1429]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[313,1273,193,1429]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54 – 57. Female genitalia of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 54, genitalia slide no. RA 655, paratype, apophyses; 55, same, bursa copulatrix; 56, genitalia slide no. RA 654, paratype, general view; 57, genitalia slide no. RA 655, paratype, comb-like pectinations on corpus bursae (ZMUC)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035622/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figs 54, 56</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1752,2029]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,392]" lastPageId="7" pageId="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,1932,1957]" pageId="6">Bionomics</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[338,469,1932,1957]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 45" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1450,1473]" captionTargetBox="[263,1305,193,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[263,1309,193,1414]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 45. Distribution and bionomics of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 40, distribution map, Ecuador; 41, habitat, semi-dry mountainous slopes at altitude about 1800 m, Vilcabamba, South of Loja, southern Ecuador; 42, 43, host plant Scutellaria volubilis Kunth; 44, 45, leaf mines" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035618/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figs 41–45</figureCitation>
). Host plant: 
<taxonomicName authority="Kunth" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1818" box="[617,938,1932,1957]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Salvia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scutellarioides">
<emphasis box="[617,859,1932,1956]" italics="true" pageId="6">Salvia scutellarioides</emphasis>
Kunth
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" authorityYear="1820" box="[949,1070,1932,1957]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lamiaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1085,1215,1932,1957]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 45" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1450,1473]" captionTargetBox="[263,1305,193,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[263,1309,193,1414]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 45. Distribution and bionomics of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 40, distribution map, Ecuador; 41, habitat, semi-dry mountainous slopes at altitude about 1800 m, Vilcabamba, South of Loja, southern Ecuador; 42, 43, host plant Scutellaria volubilis Kunth; 44, 45, leaf mines" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035618/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figs 42, 43</figureCitation>
). Egg on upper side or underside of the leaf. Larva pale to bright yellow, with pale ochre-brown intestine and grey-brown head; feeds in January and February (possibly also in late December; in February half of leaf-mines are empty, only some with very young larvae). Leaf mine is a very slender and long sinuous gallery; at the beginning, filled with black frass (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 45" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1450,1473]" captionTargetBox="[263,1305,193,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[263,1309,193,1414]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 45. Distribution and bionomics of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 40, distribution map, Ecuador; 41, habitat, semi-dry mountainous slopes at altitude about 1800 m, Vilcabamba, South of Loja, southern Ecuador; 42, 43, host plant Scutellaria volubilis Kunth; 44, 45, leaf mines" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035618/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
); further on, the gallery gradually widens, with distinctive areas of the track not filled with the frass (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 45" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1450,1473]" captionTargetBox="[263,1305,193,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[263,1309,193,1414]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 45. Distribution and bionomics of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 40, distribution map, Ecuador; 41, habitat, semi-dry mountainous slopes at altitude about 1800 m, Vilcabamba, South of Loja, southern Ecuador; 42, 43, host plant Scutellaria volubilis Kunth; 44, 45, leaf mines" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035618/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
). Larval exit slit on upper side of the leaf. Cocoon (
<figureCitation box="[787,920,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1229,1252]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,193,1208]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1247,193,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 22. Cocoons and adults. 13, 14, Stigmella lamiacifoliae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., cocoons; 15, same, forewing of male holotype; 16, same, male holotype, general view; 17, same, male paratype; 18, Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov., female paratype; 19, same, male holotype; 20, same, forewing of female paratype; 21, 22, same, cocoons" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035610/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Figs 21, 22</figureCitation>
) beige, 
<quantity box="[1015,1153,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="7" unit="mm" value="2.45" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1228,1366,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="7" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.5 mm</quantity>
wide. Adults probably fly in March–April (indoors, emerged in March).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,295,320]" pageId="7">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[361,446,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 45" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1450,1473]" captionTargetBox="[263,1305,193,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[263,1309,193,1414]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 45. Distribution and bionomics of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 40, distribution map, Ecuador; 41, habitat, semi-dry mountainous slopes at altitude about 1800 m, Vilcabamba, South of Loja, southern Ecuador; 42, 43, host plant Scutellaria volubilis Kunth; 44, 45, leaf mines" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035618/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). This species occurs in the Andes (southern 
<collectingCountry box="[958,1056,295,320]" name="Ecuador" pageId="7">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[1067,1230,295,320]" country="Ecuador" name="Loja" pageId="7">Loja Province</collectingRegion>
), usually on semidry slopes at altitude about 
<quantity box="[460,545,332,356]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="7" unit="m" value="1800.0">1800 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[560,643,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 45" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1450,1473]" captionTargetBox="[263,1305,193,1414]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[263,1309,193,1414]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 45. Distribution and bionomics of Stigmella scutellariae Remeikis &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 40, distribution map, Ecuador; 41, habitat, semi-dry mountainous slopes at altitude about 1800 m, Vilcabamba, South of Loja, southern Ecuador; 42, 43, host plant Scutellaria volubilis Kunth; 44, 45, leaf mines" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035618/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
